description.narrative: Nutrition stakeholders have improved capacities to provide quality promotional and preventive interventions to children (0-23 months), adolescent girls, and pregnant and lactating women in rural and peri-urban areas, particularly those affected by food insecurity., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 1. By 2022, newborns, children under-five, adolescents, and pregnant and lactating women, increasingly utilize quality health, nutrition HIV and Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) services and families adopt healthy and hygienic behaviours and practices, including during emergencies.

description.narrative: L'UNICEF a réalisé, la révision des documents stratégiques et normatifs à savoir : le Protocole de Prise en Charge de la Malnutrition et la Politique Nationale de Nutrition. L'UNICEF a facilité le lancement de l'Initiative Hôpital Ami des Bébés afin de promouvoir l'Allaitement Maternelle Exclusif au niveau national. Le bureau UNICEF a initié également le lancement du concept « Alimentation du nourrisson et du jeune enfant (ANJE) ». Dans les structures de santé, renforcement de capacité des prestataires de service sur la prise en charge de la malnutrition et suivi par les supervisions du programme de nutrition sur le terrain. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:14/01/2020
